entries.journalContent: My brain feels like a large bowl of mashed potatoes.
Actually not too bad. Objects seem a lot less scary after today.
Wow, the DOM now seems way less terrifying. Glad I'm starting to pick things up!
Today was a solid 50/50. I felt pretty good about â€¦nts. At least I'm not the only one at that point.

Feeling pretty great today! Once I was able to actually get in and work on modularity, I began to feel a lot more confident with it. And I've been messing around with factory functions on my own, so it's nice to be able to really implement that.

Ok, I don't totally know exactly how I did it or how any of this actually works, but this thing actually functions the way it's supposed to. I'm tired and confused, but a working product is a working product, so I'm not going to complain.
This may be the excess of coffee talking, but I feel like I actually understand array methods fairly well. Sort is a bit tricky, but I think I can get it before too long!
I think I'm actually starting to understand this stuff. Or maybe I'm crazy. Who knows?
